OL,3,CPlans to shake up Welsh school year
OL,4,Cshelved for at least four years
OL,6,FMore than half of those who responded
OL,7,Fwanted the school calendar re-
OL,8,Fstructured. Of those who responded,
OL,9,Fparents, governors, and youth workers
OL,10,Fwere broadly in favour of changes
OL,11,Fwhile teachers, unions and tourism
OL,12,Forganisations were broadly against.
OL,14,FHowever, the findings from the
OL,15,Fconsultation were equivocal and
OL,16,Fcontradictory, with more discussion
OL,17,Fand exploration next needed to ensure
OL,18,Fany future amendments benefit everyone.
