OL,3,CPlans to shake up Welsh school year
OL,4,Cshelved for at least four years
OL,6,F"Kicking this into the long grass is
OL,7,Fnot good enough, Labour cannot ignore
OL,8,Fevery teacher's union, let alone the
OL,9,Ftourism and business sectors, who are
OL,10,Fagainst the plans, the policy needs to
OL,11,Fbe scrapped completely."
OL,13,FPlaid Cymru's education spokesperson
OL,14,FHeledd Fychan MS said: "Consulting on
OL,15,Freforming the school year had been
OL,16,Fpart of the Cooperation Agreement, and
OL,17,Fas we emphasised throughout the
OL,18,Fconsultation period, it's important
OL,19,Fthat the Welsh Government listened to
OL,20,Fthe views of parents, teachers and
OL,21,Flearners.
