OL,3,CPlans to shake up Welsh school year
OL,4,Cshelved for at least four years
OL,6,F"It's clear that there is a crisis in
OL,7,Feducation in Wales. This requires
OL,8,FWelsh Government to take action to
OL,9,Fimprove school attendance, educational
OL,10,Fattainment and safety, as well as
OL,11,Frecruit and retain more teachers and
OL,12,Fimprove support for learners with
OL,13,Fadditional learning needs.
OL,15,F"Steps must also be taken to ensure no
OL,16,Fchild goes hungry in the school
OL,17,Fholidays, and I am urging the Welsh
OL,18,FGovernment to put plans in place for
OL,19,Fthe upcoming summer holiday period to
OL,20,Fsupport children and their families."
